HEADWORD: Micrology
<hw>Mi*crol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Micro-</ets> + <ets>-logy</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>That
part of science which treats of microscopic objects, or depends on
microscopic observation.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Attention to petty items or differences.</def>
<rj><au>W. Taylor.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>micromercurialism</ent>⟦br⟧
